\begin{letter}{Mathematics Search Committee\\
Department of Mathematics\\
Harvard University and MIT\\
Cambridge,
Massachusetts 02138}


\opening{Dear Search Committee,}

%
I am writing to express my interest in the Harvard University Research Scientist position. I am currently a Ph.D. candidate in Mathematics at the University of British Columbia, working under the supervision of Dr. Michael Bennett. I expect to complete my degree in June of $2019$.

My research interests lie primarily in the field of computational and algebraic number theory. My thesis work focuses on computing elliptic curves over $\mathbb{Q}$ via solutions of certain binary forms called Thue-Mahler equations. In my work with Dr. Bennett and our collaborators, Dr. Samir Siksek, Dr. Rafael von K\"{a}nel, and Dr. Benjamin Matshke, I am developing new techniques and improved Magma packages to efficiently resolve Thue-Mahler equations. While I am currently working on a paper with my collaborators on these results, variations of these packages have already been used in two papers with my advisor, and we expect at least one more paper to result from the contents of my thesis. Apart from proficiency in Magma, I am also familiar with SageMath, Unix bash, and Python.

Attached you will find my curriculum vitae. Letters in support of my application will be sent separately. You should expect letters from Dr. Michael Bennett, Dr. Andrew Rechnitzer, and Dr. Samir Siksek. Please contact me if you need any further information. Thank you for your consideration.


\closing{Sincerely,
%\includegraphics[width=6cm]{signature.pdf}
}
